  "sections": [
    { "tag": "section", "className": "hero",       "bgMode": "revival",  "bgColor": "#1a1410", "colorMode": "#e8d8b8", "childTextSnippet": "THE STILL. Everything in this bottle was within forty miles of my barn three weeks ago. [Wide photograph: copper still in dim barn light.]" },
    { "tag": "section", "className": "forage",     "bgMode": "bulletin", "bgColor": "#e8d8b8", "colorMode": "#1a1410", "childTextSnippet": "1 · FORAGE. Ramps in March. Sourwood blossom in late June. Sumac in August. Persimmon after first frost. Twenty-seven plants currently used across the line." },
    { "tag": "section", "className": "macerate",   "bgMode": "revival",  "bgColor": "#1a1410", "colorMode": "#e8d8b8", "childTextSnippet": "2 · MACERATE. Mason jars on a shelf in the barn. Maceration windows by botanical. [Photograph: the shelf, the jars, the labels.]" },
    { "tag": "section", "className": "distill",    "bgMode": "bulletin", "bgColor": "#e8d8b8", "colorMode": "#1a1410", "childTextSnippet": "3 · DISTILL. The copper still Wendell built in 2019. 40 gallons per batch. Wood-fired heat. I built the still in 2019 from a kit I bought from a man in Tennessee. He drew me a diagram on the back of a feed-store receipt. I still have the receipt." },
    { "tag": "section", "className": "label",      "bgMode": "revival",  "bgColor": "#1a1410", "colorMode": "#e8d8b8", "childTextSnippet": "4 · LABEL. The shed I bought off the widow of a dead preacher for $4,000. Hand-painted labels, one per bottle, by Wendell. Some imperfect on purpose." },
    { "tag": "section", "className": "bottle",     "bgMode": "bulletin", "bgColor": "#e8d8b8", "colorMode": "#1a1410", "childTextSnippet": "5 · BOTTLE. Glass from a guy in Knoxville. Bottled, capped, dated, shipped within thirty days of distillation." },
    { "tag": "section", "className": "botanicals", "bgMode": "bulletin", "bgColor": "#e8d8b8", "colorMode": "#3e5a3e", "childTextSnippet": "THE TWENTY-SEVEN. Plain table: sourwood blossom (Oxydendrum arboreum) · staghorn sumac (Rhus typhina) · sassafras root (Sassafras albidum) · paw-paw (Asimina triloba) · wild persimmon (Diospyros virginiana) · ramps (Allium tricoccum, spring-only) · mountain mint (Pycnanthemum) · wild ginseng (Panax quinquefolius, sustainable) · chicory root (Cichorium intybus) · eastern juniper (Juniperus virginiana) · magnolia bark (Magnolia officinalis) · black walnut hull (Juglans nigra) · muscadine grape (Vitis rotundifolia) · ... (continuing to 27)" }
  ],
